<section class="section-lg">
    <div class="container">

        <div class="row align-items-center py-5">
            <div class="col-sm-12 ">
                <h1 class="title mb-4">
                    <span class="text-info">SUMMARY</span>
                </h1>
                <p>
                    Trades are the backbone and foundation of the entire economy throughout the world. Players will remain responsible for specializing and mastering their trade to serve their unique purpose in the world and contribute to the economy
                    in the massive demand for raw materials, refined materials, and crafted items to aid everyone throughout their adventure. We strongly strive to allow the player to choose a role they desire and give them a unique purpose in the world that gives them meaning and purpose to contribute to as they wish.
                    Players will be able to specialize in two individual trades and will receive bonuses, become more effective, and be granted the ability to craft, gather or refine higher tier resources. Trades that are not specialized will be less effective, and restricted to low-mid tier options. This allows players
                    to become more of a special required role throughout the world and feel needed and become more valuable to the community rather than a 'Jack of all Trades'.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-center py-5">
            <div class="col-sm-12 ">
                <h1 class="title mb-4">
                   <span class="text-info">TRAINING METHODS</span>
                </h1>
                <p>
                    We will offer one or more training methods for specific trades to allow the player different paces to train and master their trades. These methods will contain different levels of participation for different outcomes.
                    This allows players to decide how they wish to play the game and choose the option that fits their gameplay style desires best.
                </p>
                    <h3>
                    INTERACTIVE
                    </h3>
                <p>The interactive training method is a more participation reliant method that involves a small mini-game that will allow the player to reduce the chance of failure and speed up the process of the action.</p>
                <h6>EXAMPLE</h6>
                You're cooking a piece of meat and a progress bar would appear; The progress bar would have a colored meter of when not to pull it off and when to pull it off. The experience received will be determined on how precise you are
                with pulling the piece of meat off when the progress bar tells you to. If you pull it off to early you will receive less experience or if you pull it off at the perfect time it will provide an experience bonus. Otherwise you will be rewarded with the base experience
                for the piece of meat.
                <hr>
                <h3>
                    CASUAL
                </h3>
                The casual training method would be less effective but more traditional. Allowing the player to be more relaxed while they sit and wait and not worry about precision while still being able to reasonably progress throughout the game.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-center py-5">
            <div class="col-sm-12 ">
                <h1 class="title mb-4">
                    <span class="text-info">TRADE LEVELS</span>
                </h1>
