        <div class="row align-items-center py-5">
            <div class="col-sm-12 ">
                <h1 class="title mb-4">
                    <span class="text-info">PROGRESSION</span>
                </h1>
                <p>The progression of trades as a whole follows a linear hierarchy that evolve around progression states. The trade experience is a sum of all of the trade's categories added up together to result in it's total experience.</p>

                <h4>TECHNIQUES</h4>
                <p>Techniques are considered 'sub skills' and can be classified as either a technique or style within a trade itself that a player will individually train and progress to increase their overall progression of the trade.</p>
                Experience gained through categories will count towards increasing your state within the trade as a whole. The experience needed to increase your trade state is the experience needed for a trade to reach a specific state multiplied by the number of categories within the trade.
                <hr>
            <h4>EXAMPLE</h4>
                <h6>TRADE - UNTRAINED FISHERMAN</h6>
                <small style="font-size: 14px">TECHNIQUES</small>
                <ul>
                    <li style="font-size: 14px">Untrained Cage Fisherman</li> (14,500XP needed Beginner)
                    <li style="font-size: 14px">Beginner Fly Fisherman</li> (32,750 XP needed for Apprentice)
                    <li style="font-size: 14px">Untrained Deepsea Fisherman</li> (14,500XP needed for Beginner)
                </ul>
                <p>Given the players current experience the player would currently resign at a Untrained Fisherman and would need to achieve a total experience of 43,500XP in any technique to become a Beginner Fisherman</p>
                <p>HORIZONTAL PROGRESSION</p>
                <p>A player will be able to catch low tier fish in both techniques of fly and cage - but some categories can or will be locked behind a trade state. For example; A player will not be able to do deep sea fishing until they are at-least a Journeyman in Fishing. Therefor
                they would need to achieve enough experience in Fly and Cage fishing to average themselves out to be a Journeyman Fisherman to unlock Deepsea Fishing.</p>
            </div>
